    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this new high protein dog food for my lab, he's getting up there in age (around 9) and i wanna make sure i'm getting the macros right. what's a good protein to fat ratio for an older lab so he keeps his muscle but doesn't get too heavy?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an older lab, you want a balance that supports muscle maintenance without adding unnecessary bulk. A good protein to fat ratio is often in the range of 30-35% protein and 25-30% fat. It's important to look at the specific amino acid profile too, not just the raw numbers. You can always check the label for things like essential amino acid levels to make sure he's getting what he needs.",
      "source": "target",
