      "content": "that makes sense. i've seen some brands mention \"wild-caught fish\" for the omega-3s. do you think the source of the protein matters as much as the ratio, or is it fine if it's just generic meat meal as long as the numbers are okay?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The source of the protein matters a great deal, especially when you're dealing with an older, slower-moving dog. A whole-food source, like wild-caught fish or quality poultry, generally provides a more complete and bioavailable amino acid profile than a generic meat meal. Generic meat meals are often just a mix, and sometimes they're packed with filler that doesn't help the dog's specific needs. It's better to aim for quality protein sources.",
